        public static DWord constructFromHexStr(java.lang.String hexStr)
        Returns a new DWord object from a hex string. If the string contains less than 16 hex digits, it will be right-padded with 0's. If it has more than 16 hex digits, the digits after 16 will be truncated. The string might contain underscores/spaces for readability purpose.
        Parameters:
        hexStr - the given string of hex digits
        Returns:
        a new DWord object

      • constructFromWordArr

        public static DWord constructFromWordArr(Word[] wordArr)
        Returns a new DWord object from the clone of the given Word array. If the array size is less than 2, new UBytes with value zero will be added on the right, and if it has more than 2 Words, the first 2 will be picked.
        Parameters:
        wordArr - the given array of Words that will be cloned before use
        Returns:
        a new DWord object
